properties.text: The desert of Egypt in which there are many wild animals.
Here reigns Musameli, very rich on account of the gold which is found in this river. Here the Ethiopian Christians begin to appear very poor.
The sea, or land, of sand, in which the way is found as at sea, and the people travel under cover lest the wind and sand should destroy them on the way.
The golden river is here eight leagues broad.
Passage into the land of the negroes.
The second monarchy, which in the time of Hannibal greatly harassed the Romans, and was then totally destroyed by them under Scipio.
In these mountains are many princes and kings, and they dwell continually in tents, and fight against the Saracens. There are also many strongholds and states beyond.
Here were slain the 12 peers of France.
Infidel Spain subjected to Christianity by Charles the Great, after much fighting.
Pentapolis - five main Greek colonies in the Roman province of Libya Superior.
Getulia - a large desert region south of the Atlas Mountains
Many Saracen pilgrims come here to Mecca on account of their Prophet.
Here very hairy women bring forth without males.

Abinichibel is king of the Ethiopian Saracens,
with his people having the face of a dog, and they
go naked on account of the heat of the sun.

Nubia of the Christians, the seat of Prester
John, whose empire extends from the mouth of
the Gandis to the river of gold.
Missa Sea believed to be the source of the Nile.

The part of the earth beneath the torrid zone
uninhabitable on account of the excessive heat of
the sun.
Phcenix, the sole most beautiful and solitary bird in the world, burns itself in an aromatic fire, and in three days is recreated from its ashes.
The Indian Sea in which there are 7000 islands.
Here were slain the 12 peers of France.
Infidel Spain subjected to Christianity by Charles the Great, after much fighting.

Upper India, in which is the body of the blessed Thomas. Many Christian Kingdoms. Here are an infinite number of precious amber stones. Here also are huge men having horns four feet long, and there are serpents also of such magnitude, that they can eat an ox whole.
Babylon, the first monarchy of the world.
Here Alexander vanquished Darius with fifteen thousand men in three battles.
The river Indus, where there are elephants, gold and precious stones innumerable, and no one wants for gold ornaments.
Trees preserved where Alexander and his armies were.
The distant Seres collecting silk from the trees.

Magog, in these two are races big as giants, full of evil manners, Jews whom King Artaxor collected from all parts. Province of Gog, in which the Jews were confined in the time ofArtaxor, King of Persia.
Lower India in which is the City of Cathay, and the seat of the great Canis, Emperor of the Tartars.
From here to the ocean a land uninhabitable on account of cannibalism.
From Organti to Cathagium, camels go in four months.
Mount Caucasus extends from here under many names to the East.
Mount Sinai where was given the laws of Moses.
Crossing of the children of Israel
The fountain of the sun boiling in the evening and tepid in the morning.
This region mountainous and uninhabitable on account of the excessive cold, because it is under the North Pole.
Here the body is put to be preseved by the cold.
Here are bears, white falcons and such like.
The extreme part of Norway uninhabitable on account of the excessive cold.
This race considers itself sacred, and they make of themselves a sacrifice, placing a particular head on a pole by the hair, and then they adore it on their knees until it falls.
Hyperborean mountains, in which Griffins and tigers dwell.
Here are dogs stronger than lions.
The land formerly of illustrious women.
Sinopa conquered many kingdoms and vanquished Hercula. Pampedo and Insipia subjugated Asia and Europe. Pantisalea at Troy won many battles and vanquished many Greeks.

The great district of Tartary, which the Tartars traverse with their beasts of burden and cattle as
long as there is grass.
Here they burn bodies with the items belonging to them.
Lake Ysicol, upon which rested the body of the blessed Matthew.
Here are the confines of the Pagans and Christians, who are continually fighting with .one another in Prussia.
The stag when pressed by dogs drinks water which it vomits upon them boiling.
Here cross the Bohemian forests, which extend to the Pagans
Seven Christian camps in Pagan forest.
These provinces are flat, and deserted on account of the fighting ofthe Pagans against the Christians.
Here dwell the Scythians or poor Tartars who through want sell their children and parents in the market, just as cattle amongst Christians.
Paris sine . . . pare bonitate et dominio sedet in . . . sitate planito et castelleto. (Paris without . . He sits in equal goodness and dominion in . . . situated on a plain and a fort)
King John of France taken prisoner here in battle with the Prince of Wales.
Here in Alunnia in 432, Attila King of the Huns fought against the Romans, and 180,000 were killed of both sides
Here the mountains divide Italy from Almania and Gallia. Crossing of Hannibal with 70 eliphants over the Rhone here in Ludanum.
Italy, beautiful, fertile, brave and proud, where, futile, justice wants a single lord.
Hannibal defeated the Romans here in the region of Papia.
The apostolic and imperial seat triumphed for seven years.
Battle of Cannae in which Hannibal slew 44,000 Romans, and collected from the soldiers three modia (bushels) of golden rings.
Here reposes the body of the blessed Niccolay de Baro.
Here Hasdrubal was slain, with 43,000 Carthaginians.
Athens, the sole seat of learning of the world.
Here the third monarchy ofthe world was acquired by Alexander.
Here was the great fight of Caesar and Pompey. Here Rome lost the Commonwealth.
Greece in which Basac conquered the Christians 1395, of whom he beheaded many French nobles.

Here the Greeks, with the help of a part of the world during ten years, fought against the Trojans and the other part of the world, whom by they destroyed, from which Trojans were made many kingdoms and dominions.
Mountain of Armenia where is Noah's Ark.
Savastra, where Tamburlan vanquished Basac. Of 800,000 men slew 2,000.
Here Tamaris, queen of the Scythians, slew Cyrus with 300,000.
The seat of lambec, Emperor of Mesia, borders upon the Hungarians.
